      • ordinal

        public int ordinal()
        EventType is effectively an enumeration. Since there is a known, limited number of possible types, we expose an ordinal for each in order to be able to efficiently do associations elsewhere in the codebase (array vs. Map) For the total number of types, see values()
        Returns:
        An unique ordinal for this EventType, starting at 0 and up to the number of distinct events
